highlights.text: Zach Bryan has the most spots on Top Songs USA. “28” is the highest at #14.
“Guy For That (Feat. Luke Combs)” by Post Malone and Luke Combs is the highest new entry on Top Songs USA at #12.
“Iris” by The Goo Goo Dolls is the biggest gainer on Top Songs USA, up 85 spots at #86.
“No Role Modelz” by J. Cole has been on Top Songs USA the longest, at 219 weeks straight.
